@PointCloudNiphon BTW you can use the `--profile` argument in test.py to see the timing breakdown between inference and NMS also. Hmm I suppose I should add this to detect.py as well. 
```
python3 test.py --weights ... --cfg ... --data ... --profile
```

Inference can be sped up with larger batch sizes, but NMS is run per image in all cases, so the only ways to affect it's speed currently are here. Note that the 1.6 ms profile time uses all default settings though (none of these speedups are applied).

- Increase your `conf_thres`
- Turn off `multi_cls`
- Decrease `iou_thres`
https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/blob/1dc1761f45fe46f077694e1a70472cd7eb788e0c/utils/utils.py#L504
